.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-DISCARD 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-discard \- remove live changes or reverse batch changes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch discard
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR [\fIPATH\fR] | \fB\-\-files\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
[\fB\-\-from\fR \fIBATCH\fR | \fB\-\-to\fR \fIBATCH\fR]
[\fB\-\-auto\-advance\fR|\fB\-\-no\-auto\-advance\fR]
.PP
.B git-stage-batch discard
[\fB\-\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR | \fB\-\-to\fR \fIBATCH\fR \fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-as\fR \fITEXT\fR | \fB\-\-as\-stdin\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-edge\-overlap\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B discard
removes selected live changes from the working tree. With
.B \-\-to
it first saves the selected live changes to a batch. With
.B \-\-from
it reverses changes from a batch without deleting that batch.
.PP
.B WARNING:
discarding live changes permanently removes them from the working tree unless
they are saved with
.BR \-\-to .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Discard or save only specific displayed line IDs.
.TP
.B \-\-file
.RI [ PATH ]
Operate on one complete file. If
.I PATH
is omitted, use the selected hunk's file.
.TP
.BI "\-\-files " PATTERN "..."
Operate on all changed files matched by gitignore-style patterns.
.TP
.BI "\-\-from " BATCH
Reverse changes from
.IR BATCH .
.TP
.BI "\-\-to " BATCH
Save selected live changes to
.I BATCH
before removing them from the working tree.
.TP
.BI "\-\-as " TEXT
Replace selected live content with
.IR TEXT .
For
.B \-\-file
the text becomes the full working-tree file content. For
.BR "\-\-to \-\-line" ,
the replacement is saved in the batch before the selected original lines are
removed.
.TP
.B \-\-as\-stdin
Read replacement text from standard input exactly.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-edge\-overlap
Do not strip unchanged edge-overlap lines from replacement text used with
.BR "\-\-to \-\-line \-\-as" .
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-advance
Select the next hunk after the command completes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-advance
Leave no hunk selected after the command completes.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
git-stage-batch discard --line 4-6
git-stage-batch discard --to cleanup --file src/app.py
git-stage-batch discard --from cleanup --files 'src/**'
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-include (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-apply (1)
